		<p>This looks absolutely great!<br />
I assume vanilla extract is more convenient to use as to scratch out fresh vanilla beans?</p>
<p>I thought about it &#8211; if you have anything barrel aged in the house, it could turn out even more fantastic.<br />
Oak barrels tend to flavor the spirit inside into a primary vanilla, secondary caramel, toffee, light coffee flavor.<br />
I would suggest a nice subtle barrel aged rum like Bacardi 8 or a not too spicy Bourbon [Maker's Mark].<br />
Off course then it is not that cheap anymore &#8211; but still cheaper than store bought extract and of course much soperior&#8230;</p>

